    • flagCases

      public static List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter> flagCases(List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter> listEncounters, List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbCondition> listConditions, List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbObservation> listLaborObservations, InputCodeSettings inputCodeSettings)
      Marks all encounters in the given list as SARS-CoV-2-positive or /-borderline or /-negative (Exclusion via negative diagnostic code), as far as this information can be determined from the corresponding observation and condition resources.
      Parameters:
      listEncounters - List of all UkbEncounter resources that could be flagged.
      listConditions - List of all UkbCondition resources with U07.* ICD codes.
      listLaborObservations - List of all observation resources with a SARS-CoV-2 PCR code.
      inputCodeSettings - The configuration of the parameterizable codes such as the observation codes or procedure codes.
      Returns:
      The origin encounter list, with flags about the corona status in the extension.

    • ambulantStationaryLogic

      public static void ambulantStationaryLogic(HashMap<String,Set<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter>> mapFlaggedEncounter, List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter> listEncounterAll)
      Used to flag the cases who fall under the twelve days Logic. Stationary cases who are negative, but fall under the twelve days logic are considered as positive
      Parameters:
      mapFlaggedEncounter - Map containing all encounter with SARS-CoV-2-positive flag
      listEncounterAll - List of all encounters (including the non flagged ones) that may now be flagged due to the 12-day logic.

    • flagEncounter

      public static HashMap<String,Set<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter>> flagEncounter(List<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter> listEncounters, Set<String> setPositiveLabResultCaseIds, HashMap<String,Set<String>> mapCaseIdsU071, HashMap<String,Set<String>> mapCaseIdsU072)
      Flag the encounters and store them in a map, separated according to their SARS-CoV-2 characteristics (positive/borderline/negative)
      Parameters:
      listEncounters - List of all Encounters that could be flagged
      setPositiveLabResultCaseIds - Set of all case numbers that have a positive SARS-CoV-2 laboratory result
      mapCaseIdsU071 - Map with case numbers of all cases with U07.1 diagnosis
      mapCaseIdsU072 - Map with case numbers of all cases with U07.2 diagnosis
      Returns:
      Map that assigns a list of cases to a flag (positive/borderline/negative)

    • addExtensionToEncounterIfSetContainsCaseId

      public static boolean addExtensionToEncounterIfSetContainsCaseId(de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter encounter, Set<de.ukbonn.mwtek.utilities.fhir.resources.UkbEncounter> setEncounter, Set<String> setCaseIds, org.hl7.fhir.r4.model.Extension flag)
      Used to flag a given encounter resource If the case id is not contained in the specified given case id set (e.g. all case ids with a certain diagnostic certainty on an U07.1 code), false is returned.
      Parameters:
      encounter - A given encounter resource that may be flagged
      setEncounter - A set of encounters that meet a certain criterion and to which the given encounter should be added if the extension is set.
      setCaseIds - Set of case numbers that meet a certain criterion
      flag - Extension flag to be set
      Returns:
      true/false if the extension was set to the given encounter

      Parameters:
